- SaaS: off-premises software is commonly called “software as a service”(cloud computing)
- On-Premise Software: On-Premise Software is software that is installed and runs on computers on the premises of the person or organization using the software, rather than at a remote facility such as a server farm or cloud
- System Life Cycle: 1. Planning 2. Requirement Analysis 3. Design 4. Implementation/Coding 5. Testing 6. Deploying 7. Maintenance
- Functional Testing: Functional testing is a type of testing that seeks to establish whether each application feature works as per the software requirements. 
